38 //
39 // Base class for all graph-based dynamic planners. These planners are all
40 // guaranteed to generate recursively feasible trajectories constructed
41 // using sampling-based logic.
42 //
44 
45 #ifndef FASTRACK_PLANNING_GRAPH_DYNAMIC_PLANNER_H
46 #define FASTRACK_PLANNING_GRAPH_DYNAMIC_PLANNER_H

56 template<typename S, typename E,
57  typename D, typename SD, typename B, typename SB>
58 class GraphDynamicPlanner : public Planner< S, E, D, SD, B, SB > {
59 public:
60  virtual ~GraphDynamicPlanner() {}
61 
62 protected:
63  explicit GraphDynamicPlanner()
64  : Planner<S, E, D, SD, B, SB>() {}
65 
66  // Plan a trajectory from the given start to goal states starting
67  // at the given time.
68  inline Trajectory<S> Plan(
69  const S& start, const S& goal, double start_time=0.0) const {
70  return RecursivePlan(start, {goal}, start_time, true);
71  }
72 
73  // Recursive version of Plan() that plans outbound and return trajectories.
74  // High level recursive feasibility logic is here.
75  Trajectory<S> RecursivePlan(
76  const S& start, const S& goal, double start_time, bool outbound,
77  SearhableSet<S>& viable_states, SearchableSet<S>& undecided_states);
78 
79  // Generate a sub-plan that connects two states and is dynamically feasible
80  // (but not necessarily recursively feasible).
81  virtual Trajectory<S> SubPlan(
82  const S& start, const S& goal, double start_time=0.0) const = 0;
83 }; //\class GraphDynamicPlanner
